### ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
### Two-Tier Retrieval, ParadeDB Hybrid, Bulk Ingestion Test Suite
### ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
###
### Pre-requisites:
###   1. V2__partition_two_tier_paradedb.sql migration applied
###   2. docker-compose up with paradedb/paradedb:0.19.11-pg16
###   3. Spring Boot app running with VehicleSummaryService, BulkVehicleIngestionService
###   4. At least one rich vehicle ingested (BMW M3)
###
### Endpoints tested:
###   POST /vehicles/ingest/rich     - single rich vehicle (batch embed + summary)
###   POST /vehicles/ingest/bulk     - bulk rich vehicles
###   POST /vehicles/ask/fleet       - two-tier fleet search
###   POST /vehicles/ask/hybrid      - ParadeDB vector + BM25 hybrid
###   POST /vehicles/{id}/ask        - single-vehicle ask (existing)
###   POST /vehicles/ask             - fleet ask (existing, single-tier)
###   GET  /vehicles/admin/summaries - view vehicle summaries
### ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════


### ── Phase 1: Ingest seed data ────────────────────────────────────────

### 1.1 Ingest BMW M3 Competition (rich, 14 chunks + summary)
# Ingest rich BMW M3 - full nested payload
POST http://localhost:8080/vehicles/ingest/rich
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "vehicleId": "bmw-m3-2025-competition",
  "year": 2025,
  "make": "BMW",
  "model": "M3",
  "trim": "Competition",
  "bodyStyle": "Sedan",
  "vehicleClass": "sports sedan",
  "engine": "3.0L twin-turbo inline-6 (S58)",
  "horsepower": 503,
  "torque": 479,
  "drivetrain": "RWD",
  "transmission": "8-speed M Steptronic automatic",
  "zeroToSixty": 3.4,
  "topSpeed": 180,
  "mpgCity": "16",
  "mpgHighway": "23",
  "msrp": "$76,900",
  "fuelType": "Premium gasoline",
  "features": ["M sport seats", "adaptive M suspension", "carbon fiber trim", "head-up display", "launch control"],
  "reviews": [
    {"source": "Car and Driver", "year": 2025, "score": 9, "summary": "The M3 Competition remains the benchmark sports sedan.", "pros": "Extraordinary engine, razor-sharp chassis", "cons": "Firm ride, polarizing styling"},
    {"source": "Motor Trend", "year": 2025, "score": 9, "summary": "No sports sedan does more things better."}
  ],
  "rankings": [
    {"source": "US News", "year": 2025, "category": "sports sedans", "rank": 2, "total": 18, "score": 91, "notes": "Praised for driving dynamics and engine character."},
    {"source": "Car and Driver", "year": 2025, "category": "luxury sports cars", "rank": 1, "total": 12, "score": 88, "notes": "Editors choice award winner for the third consecutive year."}
  ]
}


> {%
    client.log("Chunks: " + response.body.storedChunkIds?.length);
    client.log("Errors: " + JSON.stringify(response.body.errors));
%}

### 1.2 Ingest Tesla Model 3 (rich)
POST http://localhost:8080/vehicles/ingest/rich
Content-Type: application/json

{
